                <div class="icon-box--content">
                  <h1 class="job-title">
                    Real-Time VFX Artist
                  </h1>
                  <div class="content">
                    <date class="job-date"> </date>
                    <span class="job-intro">
                      We're looking for an experienced Real-Time VFX artist to
                      create stylised particle and visual effects for our new
                      project and original IP.
                    </span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </a>
            </div>
            <article class="job-description">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="job-description--inner">
                  <p>
                    At League of Geeks, we dedicate ourselves to crafting
                    engaging game experiences and a major part of this is having
                    fabulous visual effects! We're looking for a Real-Time VFX
                    artist to create stylised particle and visual effects for
                    our new project and original IP.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Short to long term contracts available depending on the
                    experience and availability of the applicant. Remote
                    opportunities are available. Relocation options &amp;
                    ongoing work will be considered for people who are
                    interested in full-time positions and are perfect fits for
                    the project!
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    We are committed to building one of the best working
                    environments in the world, with a genuine focus on well
                    being, skill development, and the correct ratio of pot
                    plants to humans. If you’re keen to work with one of the
                    world’s leading independent studios and help us create our
                    new, exciting original IP we’re developing in partnership
                    with
                    <a href="https://www.privatedivision.com/">
                      Private Division
                    </a>
                    , we'd love to hear from you!
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <strong>
                      Women and other underrepresented developers, please apply!
                      We pride ourselves on our inclusive work environment and
                      output, so we’d love to work with you.
                    </strong>
                  </p>
                  <h3>
                    Requirements:
                  </h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Experience building particle effects in a game engine (eg
                      Unity, Unreal).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Proficiency in Photoshop, After Effects and any other
                      tools that might help you to create professional effects,
                      such as Maya particle/dynamics, Fume etc.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Comfortable creating shaders using Shader Graph (or
                      equivalent) for VFX.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Excellent communication, creative collaboration and
                      teamwork skills.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      A commitment to working in a professional, inclusive and
                      supportive environment.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Understanding of how to make in-game special effects for
                      games, or shipped titles demonstrating your experience and
                      skill set.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3>
                    Responsibilities:
                  </h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Creation of VFX for LoG's games.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      To work with, and take direction from the Technical Artist
                      and Art Director and make revisions as needed.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Contribute to improvements in VFX production workflows and
                      pipelines.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Follow established production pipelines, procedures and
                      conventions, and to help document these where required.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Collaborate with other artists and the broader team to
                      help bring the project vision to life.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3>
                    Benefits:
                  </h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Weekly bring-your-dog-to-work day on Monday. Yeah, dogs!
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Talent development, mentorship and support.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Monthly self-directed professional development days.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Flexible work arrangement opportunities and
                      family-friendly considerations.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Menstrual, Menopause and Parental leave.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Sustainable work hours.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Friday afternoon team social events.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Annual Summer family picnic, Winter Feast and MIGW party.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Located in The Arcade, one of the world’s first videogame
                      co-working spaces.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Located in Melbourne, Australia. World’s most liveable
                      city seven years in a row.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3>
                    How to Apply:
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    Send a cover letter, an up-to-date CV and folio with
                    examples of your work to vfx.artist.job(at)leagueofgeeks.com
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <strong>
                      Important Stuff:
                    </strong>
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Application period closes on 7th September (CoB). We wish
                      for this position to commence on the 5th October.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Salary range is broad, between $68,000 p.a (AUD) -
                      $100,000 p.a (AUD), depending on experience.
                      <br />
                      Remote work options are available for this position.
                      Please raise an expression of interest if required.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Please note that due to the large volume of applications we
                    receive, there will be a slow response time but we will
                    endeavour to get back to everyone who shows interest!
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <strong>
                      COVID-19 Hiring Update:
                    </strong>
                    We’ve temporarily transitioned to a work-from-home model and
                    are continuing to interview and hire during this time. For
                    the safety of staff and applicants, all interview stages
                    will take place via video conference.
                  </p>
